---
title: Creamy Lemon Butter Chicken with Mozzarella Zucchini Rounds & Scallion Couscous
description: Lemon is our go-to ingredient for brightening up any meal, and this dish is positively bursting with citrusy goodness! Seared chicken is drizzled with a creamy, lemon-spiked pan sauce that’d taste good on pretty much anything. On the side, there’s tender roasted zucchini and scallion-studded couscous tossed with both lemon juice and zest. When life gives you lemons, you know what to do.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5e7a45486336ee1f19459513-37e902ea.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/creamy-lemon-butter-chicken-5e7a45486336ee1f19459513-55697c9d.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-lemon-butter-chicken-5e7a45486336ee1f19459513
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 680 mg
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and slice @zucchini{1} into ⅓-inch-thick rounds. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and halve @lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest 1 lemon and halve both).

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt, pepper, and remaining Tuscan Heat Spice. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}. Add @Israeli couscous{1/2%cup}; stir until toasted, ~{30%seconds}. Add ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and a pinch of salt. Cover and bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Once zucchini is tender, remove #baking sheet{} from oven. Heat broiler to high. Sprinkle zucchini with @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}. Broil until browned and crispy, ~{2-5%minutes}. > Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add remaining stock concentrates, ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @sour cream{2%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Add @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), half the lemon zest, juice from half the lemon (whole lemon for 4), half the scallion greens, salt, and pepper to #pot{} with couscous; stir to combine. > If couscous seems dry, add a splash of water.

Divide couscous, chicken, and zucchini between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken. Top with remaining scallion greens and lemon zest and serve.